properties.areaDesc: Juneau Borough and Northern Admiralty Island
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 23 at 3:23PM AKST until January 24 at 3:00PM AKST by NWS Juneau AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Wet snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 3 to 5
inches.

* WHERE...Mendenhall Valley including Juneau Airport.

* WHEN...From midnight tonight to 3 PM AKST Friday.

* IMPACTS...Rain changing to snow will make driving conditions
hazardous. These hazardous conditions could impact the morning
commute.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Rain changing to snow late evening. Expect
accumulations to increase after midnight. Amounts will widely
vary over short distances.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

For the latest road conditions call 5 1 1 or visit
511.alaska.gov.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT TONIGHT TO 3 PM AKST FRIDAY
